<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 8 月 11 日星期五 21:17:03 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[U.N.-Led Team Completes Risky Operation to Transfer Oil From Decaying Tanker]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> FSO Safer 曾威胁要泄漏或爆炸，并在红海地区造成环境和人道主义灾难<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128913"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=93CC5459-0AE3-46E2-B205-5B3515994E17&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-n-led-team-completes-risky-operation-to-transfer-oil-from-decaying-yemen-tanker-150ec6d2&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">一支国际专家小组完成了从也门红海沿岸一艘废弃油轮上转移超过一百万桶石油的任务。 《华尔街日报》的苏内·拉斯穆森 (Sune Rasmussen) 解释了这次高风险行动的利害关系。照片：Yahya Arhab/Zuma Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128913"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sune-engel-rasmussen" itemprop="url" rel="author">苏尼·恩格尔·拉斯穆森</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 11 日下午 3:22（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-n-led-team-completes-risky-operation-to-transfer-oil-from-decaying-yemen-tanker-150ec6d2"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>由联合国领导的一个国际专家小组完成了一次危险的行动，从<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-race-to-avert-an-oil-spill-that-could-cost-20-billion-to-fix-85a884ea?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">停泊在也门红海沿岸的一艘生锈的油轮</a>中吸走了超过一百万桶石油，多年来，这艘油轮一直面临爆炸或泄漏的威胁，并造成生态和人道主义灾难。 。</p><p>救援人员发起从已有 47 年历史的 FSO Safer 号上转移石油的行动两周后，这艘船在也门<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-houthis-advance-toward-long-term-cease-fire-in-yemen-afa10c9b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">八年血腥内战</a>期间被遗弃，一直搁浅在离也门北部海岸 5 英里处的地方。联合国周五表示，移交工作已经完成。</p><p>联合国秘书长安东尼奥·古特雷斯表示，石油的转移避免了“一场可能造成巨大的环境和人道主义灾难”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834289?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 6 月，FSO Safer 油轮在也门海岸附近进行石油转运作业。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Osamah Abdulrahman/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>据联合国称，自 2019 年以来，这艘油轮的腐蚀状况引起了国际组织和专家的警惕，他们担心大量石油泄漏到该地区脆弱的生态系统中，清理费用可能高达 200 亿美元。如果排放出来的石油将达到五分之一。历史上最大规模的油轮漏油事件扰乱了世界上最繁忙的航道之一，并关闭了向这个饱受战争蹂躏的国家运送人道主义援助的港口。</p><p>由于也门胡塞武装拒绝了国际组织进入油轮的请求，该行动已被推迟多年。在总部位于也门的法赫姆集团（Fahem Group）的调解下，该公司通过附近的荷台达港进口谷物，并说服叛军相信泄漏也会损害他们的经济和政治利益，去年达成了一项解决该问题的协议。</p><p>整个过程花费了两个多月的时间。 5月下旬，荷兰打捞公司SMIT的65名船员抵达现场评估该船的状况。他们检查了生锈的船体，更换了有缺陷的部件，并向储罐中注入惰性气体以降低爆炸风险。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="402" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834293?width=700&amp;height=402" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">替代油轮 Nautica 号在也门海岸被拖曳，与腐烂的 FSO Safer 号平行。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：安全技术委员会/来自路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>评估结束后，联合国购买的一艘超大型原油运输船排列在“安全号”旁边，两艘船的油罐用管道连接起来，然后用液压泵输送石油。转移工作于 7 月 25 日开始，两周后，当地时间周五下午 6 点完成。</p><p>预计在 10 天内，装有石油的打捞船将被运往附近地点，并固定在用粗缆绳固定在海床上的特制强化浮标上。</p><p> FSO Safer 最终将被拖到附近的一个港口（具体位置尚未确定），在那里将清除污泥，约占石油总量的 2%，相当于约 22,000 桶石油。</p><p>转让的完成虽然带来了立竿见影的缓解，但也引发了一系列新的纠纷。 FSO Safer 及其内容属于也门政府，但现在总部设在亚丁的被推翻的政府和占领首都萨那的胡塞武装都声称自己是也门的合法统治者。</p><p>目前尚未就石油的命运达成任何协议。如果出售，双方必须就利润如何处理达成一致。如果要将其储存在新的替换船上，则必须筹集资金用于油轮的运营。</p><p>联合国仍然缺乏资金来完成剩余的任务。联合国开发计划署署长阿奇姆施泰纳周五告诉记者，联合国的计划是清理 FSO Safer 中的污泥，并将其在绿色回收场进行废弃，利用利润来弥补资金缺口。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=93CC5459-0AE3-46E2-B205-5B3515994E17&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-n-led-team-completes-risky-operation-to-transfer-oil-from-decaying-yemen-tanker-150ec6d2&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">一个国际专家小组已开始努力在一艘废弃油轮上转移超过一百万桶石油，以免其从也门红海沿岸泄漏。 《华尔街日报》的苏尼·拉斯穆森 (Sune Rasmussen) 解释了这一高风险行动的利害关系。照片：Yahya Arhab/Zuma Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>施泰纳表示，但这还不足以弥补资金短缺，并呼吁商业参与者提供帮助。</p><p> “让我也在这里非常坦率地说这一点，”他说。 “我认为业内有许多人可能仍会抓住这个时机，在他们迄今尚未采取行动的领域迈出一步，帮助缩小这一融资缺口。”</p><p>写信给 Sune Engel Rasmussen： <a href="mailto:sune.rasmussen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sune.rasmussen@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 19:22:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/un-led-team-completes-risky-operation-to-transfer-oil-from-decaying-yemen-tanker-150ec6d2</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/un-led-team-completes-risky-operation-to-transfer-oil-from-decaying-yemen-tanker-150ec6d2<author><![CDATA[Sune Engel Rasmussen]]></author><category>海运</category><category>货运/物流</category><category>海运</category><category>水路运输/航运</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>发展/人道主义援助</category><category>国际关系</category><category>灾害/事故</category><category>自然环境</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>环境污染</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>发展</category><category>人道主义援助</category><category>国际关系</category><category>灾难</category><category>事故</category><category>自然环境</category><category>政治</category><category>环境污染</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>海运</category><category>货运</category><category>后勤</category><category>海运</category><category>水运</category><category>船运</category><category>运输</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iran Slows Buildup of Near-Weapons-Grade Enriched Uranium]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>拜登政府希望德黑兰停止积累高浓缩铀，以此作为缓解紧张局势的一步<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128794"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="521" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834154?width=860&amp;height=521" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">伊朗纳坦兹铀浓缩设施的离心机。自美国退出 2015 年伊朗核协议以来，德黑兰大规模扩大了其计划。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128794"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/laurence-norman" itemprop="url" rel="author">劳伦斯·诺曼</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 11 日下午 1:17 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-slows-buildup-of-near-weapons-grade-enriched-uranium-492df473"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>伦敦——知情人士周五表示，伊朗已大幅放慢了积累近武器级浓缩铀的速度，并稀释了部分库存，此举可能有助于缓解与美国的紧张关系，并允许恢复伊朗核计划。就<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-could-produce-nuclear-weapon-in-several-months-if-it-decides-to-do-so-mark-milley-says-ecd38f07?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其有争议的核计划进行更广泛的讨论。</a></p><p>德黑兰积累高浓缩铀的速度越慢，其用于核武器的潜在裂变材料就越少。</p><p>这一消息发布的前一天<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-releases-four-americans-from-evin-prison-b396ee09?mod=world_major_2_pos1&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，伊朗将四名美国公民从监狱中软禁起来</a>，这是计划中的囚犯交换的第一步，华盛顿预计他们最终将返回家园。如果美国被拘留者获释，伊朗将获得因美国制裁而被困在韩国的数十亿美元石油收入。</p><p>美国和欧洲官员告诉伊朗，如果夏季紧张局势缓和，他们将在今年晚些时候进行更广泛的谈判，包括就伊朗核计划进行谈判。</p><p>对于拜登政府来说，希望在明年总统选举之前避免与德黑兰发生任何重大危机。华盛顿和其他地方的批评者表示，美国正准备奖励伊朗劫持美国公民并小幅暂停其核工作，而德黑兰却加大了地区威胁，并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-expands-military-aid-to-russia-amid-war-in-ukraine-u-s-says-e1c819cd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">为俄罗斯</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-sea-drones-alter-balance-of-power-in-black-sea-391cebee?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对乌克兰的战争</a>提供军事援助。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=3EF0C42D-95E2-4D6C-A3B3-D34D9D232BB9&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Firan-slows-buildup-of-near-weapons-grade-enriched-uranium-492df473&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美国和伊朗官员表示，伊朗已从臭名昭著的德黑兰监狱释放了五名美国人，并寻求释放数十亿美元的冻结收入作为回报。美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯表示，将继续执行对伊朗的制裁。照片：克里夫·欧文/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>自美国退出<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-to-withdraw-u-s-from-iran-accord-1525800212?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">2015年伊朗核协议</a>（该协议解除了对德黑兰的国际制裁，以换取对其核工作严格但暂时的限制）以来，德黑兰大规模扩大了其计划。拜登政府上任时曾试图恢复核协议，但这些谈判去年破裂了。</p><p>西方官员最担心的工作之一是德黑兰生产 60% 的浓缩铀，美国官员表示，这些浓缩铀可以在不到两周的时间内转化为足以制造核弹的武器级材料。</p><h3>动作看起来是有意的</h3><p>美国官员曾希望德黑兰停止积累 60% 的浓缩铀，作为双方采取的一系列缓和紧张局势的措施之一，其中包括囚犯协议。</p><p>据知情人士透露，伊朗最近几周稀释了少量60%的浓缩铀，并放慢了积累新材料的速度。自 5 月份记录伊朗拥有 114 公斤高浓缩铀以来，伊朗的库存有所增加，但它很容易稀释其生产的 60% 的铀，以恢复到这一水平。目前尚不清楚德黑兰是否计划这样做。</p><p> 2 月至 5 月期间，伊朗库存平均增加了近 9 公斤，增加了 60%。</p><p>联合国原子能机构预计将在八月底或九月初发布有关伊朗核计划的下一份报告。</p><p>虽然伊朗的浓缩铀生产率可能会因多种技术原因而波动——包括其两座核设施之一的维护工作——但伊朗稀释了一些高浓缩铀的事实强烈表明，缓慢积累 60% 的材料是有意为之。</p><p>尽管如此，即使德黑兰确实停止积累 60% 的材料，它也拥有足够制造至少两枚核弹的材料。美国官员表示，今年伊朗可能在几个月内部署核武器。</p><p>伊朗驻国际原子能机构代表团没有立即回应置评请求。国际原子能机构也没有。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-launches-quiet-diplomatic-push-with-iran-to-cool-tensions-2f45af3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">今年春天，美国和伊朗高级官员举行秘密间接会谈后，</a>拜登政府官员提出了希望德黑兰采取的几项缓解紧张局势的措施。他们表示，除了停止积累60%的物资外，还希望伊朗能够与国际原子能机构表现出更好的合作，停止伊朗或其代理人对美国军队和人员的袭击。</p><p>作为交换，伊朗将获得韩国冻结的约 60 亿美元的能源销售收入，并可能获得国际货币基金组织的其他资金。</p><h3>延误的风险</h3><p>尽管拜登政府基本上放弃了恢复 2015 年与伊朗核协议的希望，但美国官员继续公开表示，他们正在寻求通过外交手段避免核危机。如果缓和局势的努力取得成果，双方可能会在 9 月份的联合国大会期间举行会晤并规划进一步的谈判。</p><p>据美国和欧洲官员称，本周四名美国囚犯被释放是双轨计划的第一步。第五名美国公民被软禁。</p><p>外交官们表示，第一阶段，美国被拘留者将从监狱获释，条件是伊朗将高达 60 亿美元的石油收入从韩国转移到瑞士，这代表了美国在伊朗的利益。作为第二步，可能需要几周时间，一旦来自韩国的伊朗资金到达卡塔尔的银行，美国公民将被允许离开伊朗。伊朗可以进入卡塔尔的银行，但华盛顿一直在密切监视。</p><p>美国官员本周警告称，他们仍在努力转移韩国资金，并警告说，被拘留者的最终释放可能会因德黑兰的分歧或与伊朗出现新的热点问题而推迟。</p><p>美国官员坚称，伊朗只能使用这些资金购买用于人道主义目的的食品和医疗用品。批评人士称，这笔钱将释放伊朗政府的其他资金，用于更邪恶的目的。</p><p>就在战俘问题和近武器级材料浓缩问题开始朝着正确方向发展之际， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/drone-strike-that-killed-u-s-contractor-in-syria-was-launched-by-iran-backed-militia-in-iraq-3a5e368a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">自 3 月底一名美国承包商被杀以来，德黑兰或其代理人</a>并未对该地区的美军发动严重袭击。</p><p>然而，在过去几周，由于伊朗对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-deploys-advanced-f-35-jets-destroyer-to-middle-east-to-brush-back-iranian-forces-7d9a92cf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">海湾航运的威胁，美国已向海湾紧急派遣飞机、舰艇和海军陆战队</a>，这是一次不同寻常的大规模部署。</p><p>高级官员亨利·罗马（Henry Rome）表示：“某些地区的局势有选择性地降级，而另一些地区的升级则有所升级，我认为，总体而言，双方都可能寻求缓解紧张局势，但他们对降级范围有不同的定义。”华盛顿近东政策研究所研究员。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——华盛顿的迈克尔·R·戈登 (Michael R. Gordon) 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给劳伦斯·诺曼，邮箱： <a href="mailto:laurence.norman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">laurence.norman@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:17:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-slows-buildup-of-near-weapons-grade-enriched-uranium-492df473</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-slows-buildup-of-near-weapons-grade-enriched-uranium-492df473<author><![CDATA[Laurence Norman]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>核武器计划</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>武器计划</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>核武器计划</category><category>政治</category><category>武器计划</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukraine’s Zelensky Fires Draft Officers After Alleged Corruption Hobbles Recruitment]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>随着战争的持续，基辅面临着日益严峻的集兵挑战<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128675"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="587" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834244?width=860&amp;height=587" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乌克兰总统泽连斯基在 Telegram 上表示，“领导这个体系的人必须确切地知道这场战争是什么”。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：谢尔盖·多尔任科/Shutterstock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128675"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/anastasiia-malenko" itemprop="url" rel="author">阿纳斯塔西娅·马伦科</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 11 日下午 1:03 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-zelensky-fires-draft-officers-after-alleged-corruption-hobbles-recruitment-a16b835c"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>乌克兰总统弗拉基米尔·泽伦斯基表示，他正在解雇地区征兵委员会的负责人，以消除腐败制度，因为该国武装部队在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-uses-small-unit-tactics-to-retake-captured-territory-from-russia-d9ef32a3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">缓慢的反攻</a>中正在努力突破俄罗斯的阵地。</p><p>周五的举措是在一系列针对招聘办公室负责人的不当行为指控之后做出的，这些指控包括伪造文件帮助男性逃避征兵以及对下属进行身体虐待等。此次行动正值战争的关键时刻，乌克兰在集结向南部和东部推进以及收复去年入侵期间被俄罗斯军队夺走的领土所需的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-year-into-war-ukraine-faces-challenges-mobilizing-troops-64dcdc49?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">部队</a>方面面临着越来越大的挑战。</p><p> “领导这个体系的人必须确切地知道战争是什么，以及为什么战争中的愤世嫉俗和贿赂是叛国行为，”泽伦斯基在与该国安全与国防委员会会面后在 Telegram 上表示。</p><p>该委员会由乌克兰执法机构的代表组成，建议乌克兰武装部队总司令瓦列里·扎卢日尼(Valeriy Zaluzhniy)用直接参与作战行动的官员填补这些职位。潜在的替代者在上任之前将接受该国安全部门的额外检查。</p><p>这一改革表明，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰试图占领俄罗斯阵地</a>并收复失地之际，寻找足够的军队变得越来越重要。</p><p>根据 4 月份泄露的美国高度机密文件显示，俄罗斯入侵时乌克兰有 26 万常备军，其中在基辅发起反攻之前已有 17,500 人被杀。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834246?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">基辅的一家军品商店。俄罗斯入侵时，乌克兰有26万常备军。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：斯宾塞·普拉特/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>军方依靠爱国热情来补充队伍，但越来越依赖征召被禁止出境的人员。身着军装的征兵军官在公共场所发出传票，与一些试图逃避应征入伍或逃往国外的男子玩猫捉老鼠的游戏。</p><p>一些男子试图通过向当地征兵办公室的官员行贿来逃避服役。</p><p>基辅表示，乌克兰人口还不到俄罗斯人口的三分之一，这还不包括战争开始以来数百万人外逃的情况，这使得<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-races-to-forge-new-army-ahead-of-offensive-aec3a1f2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">筹集足够军队的工作</a>变得更加复杂。</p><p>本周早些时候，乌克兰国家调查局在 Telegram 上报道称，该局正在调查 112 起与领土招聘中心员工滥用职权有关的刑事案件。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=AC3C107B-9782-4818-8597-CDA6782368C6&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fukraines-zelensky-fires-draft-officers-after-alleged-corruption-hobbles-recruitment-a16b835c&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> 2012 年停产后，“星光”导弹正在重新投入生产，以帮助乌克兰的防空。 《华尔街日报》研究了英国导弹如何在同类导弹中脱颖而出，以及为什么其独特的功能使其能够超越俄罗斯的反制措施。插图：赵安妮<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>该局表示，中央在反攻动员工作中发挥的关键作用，并不妨碍一些官员“为了个人利益而无视良心和国家命运的责任”。</p><p> 6 月下旬，当涉及敖德萨征兵委员会主席叶夫亨·鲍里索夫 (Yevhen Borysov) 的案件时，政府将注意力转向了征兵军官。</p>乌克兰媒体报道他的家人在战争期间在西班牙购买房产后引起了全国关注。泽连斯基指示扎卢日内立即解雇鲍里索夫。<p></p><p>此后，鲍里索夫面临调查局非法致富和逃避职业责任的指控。他此前曾表示自己没有参与任何不当行为。</p><p>这波检查包括乌克兰国家预防腐败局对生活方式的监控。该机构负责人奥列克桑德尔·诺维科夫在电视采访中表示，该机构优先检查所有征兵中心领导人及其家人的财务活动。</p><p>写信给阿纳斯塔西娅·马伦科（Anastasiia Malenko）： <a href="mailto:anastasiia.malenko@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">anastasiia.malenko@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:03:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-zelensky-fires-draft-officers-after-alleged-corruption-hobbles-recruitment-a16b835c</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-zelensky-fires-draft-officers-after-alleged-corruption-hobbles-recruitment-a16b835c<author><![CDATA[Anastasiia Malenko]]></author><category>乌克兰</category><category>受贿</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基</category><category>瓦列里·扎卢日尼</category><category>叶夫亨·鲍里索夫</category><category>亚历山大·诺维科夫</category><category>受贿</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Merrick Garland Names David Weiss as Special Counsel in Hunter Biden Investigation]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>司法部长表示，韦斯作为特拉华州的美国检察官处理调查，他请求任命<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128628"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834098?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">司法部长梅里克·加兰试图与亨特·拜登的调查保持距离。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Chip Somodevilla/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128628"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sadie-gurman" itemprop="url" rel="author">Sadie Gurman</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/aruna-viswanatha" itemprop="url" rel="author">Aruna Viswanatha</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 11 日中午 12:22 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/merrick-garland-names-david-weiss-as-special-counsel-in-hunter-biden-investigation-a2ad0ba4"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——周五，司法部长梅里克·加兰任命特拉华州联邦检察官大卫·韦斯为特别检察官，继续对亨特·拜登进行调查，在他的父亲、总统拜登<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-and-hunter-biden-ignores-political-perils-and-embraces-scandal-plagued-son-f105aee2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">竞选总统</a>之际，这为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-limbo-republicans-749b5187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">这场长期上演的法律剧</a>开启了充满政治色彩的新篇章。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-and-hunter-biden-ignores-political-perils-and-embraces-scandal-plagued-son-f105aee2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">-选举</a>。</p><p>加兰在一份简短的声明中表示，韦斯周二告诉他，他的调查“已经达到了他应该继续担任特别检察官的工作的阶段，他要求被任命为特别检察官”。</p><p>写信给 Sadie Gurman <a href="mailto:sadie.gurman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">(sadie.gurman@wsj.com)</a>和 Aruna Viswanatha ( <a href="mailto:aruna.viswanatha@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">aruna.viswanatha@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 16:22:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/merrick-garland-names-david-weiss-as-special-counsel-in-hunter-biden-investigation-a2ad0ba4</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/merrick-garland-names-david-weiss-as-special-counsel-in-hunter-biden-investigation-a2ad0ba4<author><![CDATA[Sadie GurmanAruna Viswanatha]]></author><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>亨特·拜登</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[African Force to Reverse Niger Coup Could Take Months]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>地区集团呼吁动用待命部队以恢复秩序，但似乎对其意图含糊不清<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128355"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="550" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834025?width=860&amp;height=550" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼日尔总统穆罕默德·巴祖姆在上个月末的一场政变中被废黜。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：伊芙琳·霍克斯坦/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001128355"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/michael-m-phillips" itemprop="url" rel="author">迈克尔·M·菲利普斯 (Michael M. Phillips)</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/benoit-faucon" itemprop="url" rel="author">伯努瓦·福孔 (Benoit Faucon)</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 11 日上午 11:50 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/african-force-to-reverse-niger-coup-could-take-months-95962335"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>内罗毕——本周，11个西非国家的领导人加强了使用武力推翻<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-president-us-fumble-russia-africa-86cf1454-33d18bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">尼日尔政变</a>的威胁，但西方和非洲官员表示，尝试如此雄心勃勃的行动可能需要数月时间。</p><p>西非国家经济共同体（西非经共体）领导人周四启动了一支地区待命部队，并下令部署该部队“以恢复宪法秩序”。尼日尔上个月高级军官罢免了民选总统穆罕默德·巴祖姆。</p><p>然而，西非集团似乎对其意图含糊其辞。该组织主席尼日利亚总统博拉·艾哈迈德·蒂努布称使用武力是“最后的手段”，西非经共体主席奥马尔·图雷则强调该组织“继续致力于通过和平手段恢复宪法秩序”。</p><p>这些混杂的信息让美国官员急于弄清楚西非国家经济共同体的武力威胁是否是在虚张声势。政变发生后，西非国家经济共同体立即给军政府一周的时间交出权力，但<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/deadline-for-niger-coup-leaders-to-back-down-passes-without-intervention-c6e85794?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">截止日期已过，但没有采取任何行动</a>。</p><p> “每个人都对西非国家经济共同体最近的声明感到困惑，”一位美国高级国防官员表示。 “他们没有调动军队，也没有采取很多措施来为军事干预做准备。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=7F7AB6E6-CE60-46D3-B0B7-C075C1006060&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fafrican-force-to-reverse-niger-coup-could-take-months-95962335&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">尼日尔政变领导人宣布关闭其领空，导致全国各地的航班改道。与此同时，其他西非国家为军政府设定的周日最后期限已经过去。照片：Flightradar24.com<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>这位美国官员表示，来自<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-africa-u-s-trained-militaries-are-ousting-civilian-governments-in-coups-11649505601?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">马里、布基纳法索和几内亚</a>的支持政变的反威胁可能会阻止西非经共体集团采取行动，这些国家的军政府本身是通过武力上台的。这位美国官员表示，目前掌握权力的尼日尔武装部队拥有丰富的战斗经验，其中一些是该地区最有效的武装部队之一，这也可能让西非经共体犹豫不决。</p><p>西非经共体一个成员国的一名高级陆军指挥官预测，需要六个月的时间才能准备好干预尼日尔的政变。西非经共体待命部队是非洲五支此类区域部队之一，但在被要求进行干预之前，它们更多地存在于纸面上而不是现实中。</p><p>陆军指挥官将西非待命部队描述为“一个空壳”，成员国必须用部队和装备来填补。</p><p>乔治华盛顿大学国际事务教授保罗·威廉姆斯（Paul Williams）在社交媒体平台 X（以前称为 Twitter）上写道：“没有集结、集结的军事力量在某处待命，准备立即部署。”</p><p>与此同时，尼日尔军政府没有表现出任何退缩的迹象。本周，美国代理副国务卿维多利亚·纽兰 (Victoria Nuland) 与准将进行了会谈。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-us-trained-general-65b5ecd6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">尼日尔新任国防参谋长</a>穆萨·萨拉乌·巴尔穆将军没有采取任何明显的行动来恢复民选政府。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="495" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834019?width=700&amp;height=495" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼日尔首都尼亚美军政府的支持者。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：luff/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>周五，巴尔穆没有回应就军政府计划如何应对西非经共体威胁发表评论的请求。</p><p>自从总统卫队发起起义以来，被废黜的总统巴祖姆、他的妻子和 21 岁的儿子一直被限制在首都尼亚美的住所内。</p><p>一位西方官员和与他交谈过的人士表示，过去两天，军政府在巴祖姆周围加强了 70 名警卫的安保。知情人士称，警卫人员还派出一架无人机飞越该宅邸，以回应有关法国士兵进入该宅邸的未经证实的谣言。</p><p>据西方官员和与巴祖姆交谈过的人士透露，巴祖姆在与法国总统埃马纽埃尔·马克龙的电话中报告说，军政府已经切断了官邸的电源，并警告他的家人很快就会耗尽水。据接近巴祖姆的人士透露，他在给国务卿安东尼·布林肯的电话中也发出了同样的警告。据与巴祖姆交谈过的人士透露，一名负责日常医疗检查的医生不再被允许探望巴祖姆及其家人。纽兰说，军政府拒绝了她探望被废黜总统的请求。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="477" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834020?width=700&amp;height=477" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼亚美的一个市场。美国在尼日尔驻有1100名士兵。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>欧盟外交政策负责人表示，欧盟“重申对总统被拘留条件不断恶化深感担忧”</p>何塞普·博雷尔周五在网上发布了这一消息。<p></p><p>尼日尔前殖民国家法国将巴祖姆的监禁描述为“绑架”。法国拒绝从该国撤出正在与基地组织和伊斯兰国武装分子作战的1500名士兵，理由是巴祖姆既没有辞职也没有切断尼日尔与法国的安全协议。</p><p>美国在尼日尔有 1,100 名士兵，驻扎在两个无人机基地和三个突击队哨所，训练和支持包括巴尔穆在内的尼日尔特种部队。在巴祖姆被推翻之前，美国与尼日尔军方关系非常密切，并将尼日尔视为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其西非反恐政策</a>的基石。</p><p>如果国务院宣布巴祖姆推翻政变，美国法律将要求撤回大部分军事援助。</p><p>写信给 Michael M. Phillips ( <a href="mailto:Michael.Phillips@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Michael.Phillips@wsj.com)</a>和 Benoit Faucon ( <a href="mailto:benoit.faucon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">benoit.faucon@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:50:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/african-force-to-reverse-niger-coup-could-take-months-95962335</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/african-force-to-reverse-niger-coup-could-take-months-95962335<author><![CDATA[Michael M. PhillipsBenoit Faucon]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>叛乱</category><category>武装部队</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>奥马尔·图雷</category><category>保罗·威廉姆斯</category><category>维多利亚·纽兰</category><category>穆萨·萨劳·巴尔穆</category><category>穆罕默德·巴祖姆</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>叛乱</category><category>武装部队</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China’s Options for Retaliation Are Few After U.S. Investment Ban]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>分析师表示，鉴于资金流动不对称和国内经济疲软，北京不太可能采取美国的限制措施<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001127971"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834066?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">北京正在寻求维持与华盛顿的外交解冻。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：托马斯·彼得/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001127971"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/liza-lin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Liza Lin</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dan-strumpf" itemprop="url" rel="author">Dan Strumpf</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 11 日上午 8:40（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-options-for-retaliation-are-few-after-u-s-investment-ban-f539102e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>中国不太可能因<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">拜登政府对某些中国科技公司实施新的投资禁令而</a>对美国进行反击。分析人士表示，这是因为北京方面发动猛烈攻击的能力和愿望都有限。</p><p>美国科技公司对中国投资的依赖程度不像中国科技公司对美国资本的依赖程度。他们表示，中国还在努力应对宏观经济状况恶化和投资者信心下降的问题，这使其不太可能升级经济僵局。在政治方面，北京也在寻求维持与华盛顿的外交解冻。</p><p>本周，美国发布了一项行政命令，禁止美国人投资开发先进半导体和量子计算机的中国公司，并要求美国投资者就其他类型半导体和人工智能的投资通知华盛顿。这些限制将于明年实施， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-poised-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">这将加剧这两个主要竞争对手之间关于谁控制下一代关键技术的竞争</a>。</p><p>中国商务部周四表示，美国的行为偏离了市场规范，美国正在扰乱全球供应链和贸易。中国外交部谴责这些举动是美国“公然的经济胁迫和科技欺凌”，并补充说中国将采取行动保护自己的权利。</p><p>尽管有这些言论，但分析人士和商界人士认为，对外投资措施不足以改变双方都在努力改善的紧张双边关系。中国很早就知道此类措施即将出台，一些人表示，新规定没有许多人担心的那么严格，而且目标范围更窄——至少目前的形式是这样。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=607DAEAC-FDF3-4309-B753-4A08C846B405&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fchinas-options-for-retaliation-are-few-after-u-s-investment-ban-f539102e&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">从喷气式飞机到电动汽车再到超级计算机，《华尔街日报》与不同的行业和技术专家讨论了两国在设计、工程和战略方面的匹配情况。照片插图：迈克尔·塔布和盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>相反，北京更有可能在其他领域进行报复，例如<strong>&nbsp;</strong>对中国具有重大影响力和控制权的关键材料（如稀土或特定矿物）实施更多出口限制。</p><p>拜登总统周四在一次政治筹款活动上发表讲话，提到了中国经济疲软及其领导人面临的问题。拜登表示：“在很多情况下，中国是一颗定时炸弹。”他指出，中国青年失业率很高，劳动力老龄化。</p><p>不过，他表示，他希望与北京建立“理性关系”。 “我不想伤害中国，”他在犹他州说。</p><p> 7月，中国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-restricts-exports-of-two-metals-used-in-high-performance-chips-a649402b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对镓和锗设置了出口限制</a>，美国和专家称这两种矿物是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-latest-export-controls-prompt-countries-to-explore-supply-chain-diversification-318e74d1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">生产半导体、导弹系统和太阳能电池的关键</a>。专家认为，北京此举是对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-considers-new-curbs-on-ai-chip-exports-to-china-56b17feb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">美国旨在遏制北京高科技产业的出口限制</a>的报复。</p><p> “我们预计中国会采取一些高调但不会升级的行动进行报复，”风险咨询公司欧亚集团地质技术业务主管陆晓萌表示。她预测，当局将对涉及美国公司的并购交易做出严厉的判断，或者尝试进一步限制中国的出口管制。</p><p>卢表示，该命令的直接影响有限，因为美国已经对这些行业实施了事先限制，而且中美之间的跨境投资流量已处于历史低位。她补充说，今年第一季度，美国风险投资和私募股权公司对中国的投资锐减至约 4 亿美元，而 2021 年的峰值约为 350 亿美元。</p><p>新加坡国立大学政治学副教授贾伊恩·庄 (Ja Ian Chong) 表示，从长远来看，中国将加大寻找受限制的美国技术替代品的力度，包括利用代理购买或投资可以接触到的外国公司。等关键技术。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834073?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">财政部长珍妮特·耶伦上个月在北京与中国副总理何立峰会面时表示，美国无意威胁中国的发展。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：POOL/来自路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>美国和中国是否会采取新一波针锋相对的措施是各国政府和专家正在关注的问题。</p><p>继美国之前采取的措施之后，中国对华盛顿进行了反击，有时力度更为有限。</p><p>一年前，当时任众议院议长<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/nancy-pelosi">南希·佩洛西</a>访问台湾时， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-boasts-of-ability-to-blockade-taiwan-as-military-exercises-continue-11659695158?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国以连续数天的大规模军事演习作为回应</a>，停止了与华盛顿在气候等问题上的合作，并冻结了一些军事接触。 2018年和2019年，由于两国在贸易战期间都征收关税，北京方面更难对华盛顿的措施进行相应的报复，因为它从美国进口的产品减少了</p><p>美国是一个庞大且成熟的风险投资市场，两国之间的资金流动不对称。</p><p>新的行政命令发布之际，拜登政府再次努力与北京重新接触，以制止长达数月的不断恶化的关系。</p><p>最近的努力包括上个月国务卿安东尼·布林肯对中国的访问</p>和财政部长珍妮特·耶伦。访问期间， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yellen-trip-aids-fragile-effort-by-u-s-china-to-keep-talking-9b78ea55?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">耶伦试图保证</a>美国不会威胁中国的整体发展，任何行动都仅以国家安全为由。<p></p><p>周四，中国官方媒体强调了她的言论与新投资限制之间的矛盾。中国官方媒体新华社的一篇社论指责美国在美国高级官员访问中国后推出这些措施，并向当局保证他们无意与中国脱钩，从而发出了相互矛盾的信号。</p><p> While the new rules have already provoked Beijing&#39;s ire, “there is a conscious effort by Biden to lower the US-China temperature,” Edison Lee, a technology analyst at investment bank Jefferies, wrote in a research note Thursday.</p><p> More broadly, others argue that there is a limit to China&#39;s willingness to follow through on its threats, given its economic woes. Data released this week showed the Chinese economy may be mired in a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">deflationary cycle,</a> with consumer prices in July having fallen for the first time since 2021. This adds to other signs of economic distress including <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-exports-fall-at-steepest-pace-since-february-2020-e930246b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">falling exports</a> , high <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-youth-unemployment-xi-jobs-522028c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">youth unemployment</a> and a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/country-garden-chinas-largest-surviving-developer-sinks-into-debt-crisis-2a525173?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">prolonged real estate slump</a> .</p><p> “Given the precarious macroeconomic conditions in China at the moment, they can&#39;t really risk additional retaliation that would deter third-country investment in China,” said Emily Benson, a senior fellow focused on trade and technology at the Center for Strategic and International Studies.</p><p> In addition, she said the Biden administration rules are still in a draft stage. Given the back and forth between industry and government that typically precedes the final implementation of any such regulations, it could be as long as a year before the final rules take shape and are implemented, she said.</p><p> “Nothing is set in stone,” she said, describing the proposed rules as the White House&#39;s “wishlist.”</p><p> Write to Liza Lin at <a href="mailto:liza.lin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">liza.lin@wsj.com</a> and Dan Strumpf at <a href="mailto:Dan.Strumpf@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Dan.Strumpf@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 12:40:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-options-for-retaliation-are-few-after-us-investment-ban-f539102e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-options-for-retaliation-are-few-after-us-investment-ban-f539102e<author><![CDATA[Liza LinDan Strumpf]]></author><category> Regulation/Government Policy</category><category> Corporate/Industrial News</category><category> Political/General News</category><category>国际关系</category><category>Politics/International Relations</category><category> Content Types</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E Industry News Filter</category><category> SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>government policy</category><category> corporate</category><category> industrial news</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category> international relations</category><category>政治</category><category>content types</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e industry news filter </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Here’s What a $5 Million Retirement Looks Like in America]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Retirees open up about their financial lives and how they spend their time and money <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832718/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="Retiree Pat Frey, in pink, regularly takes nature walks with a friend." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Retiree Pat Frey, in pink, regularly takes nature walks with a friend. Rebecca Stumpf for The Wall Street Journal <span>Rebecca Stumpf for The Wall Street Journal</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122102"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122102"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/veronica-dagher" itemprop="url" rel="author">Veronica Dagher</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/anne-tergesen" itemprop="url" rel="author">Anne Tergesen</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 11, 2023 5:30 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/heres-what-a-5-million-retirement-looks-like-in-america-1abc76d9"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> No amount of money can make retirement worry-free, but $5 million might come close.</p><p> Few Americans manage to save anywhere near that sum in their 401(k)s and individual retirement accounts. A $5 million retirement nest egg puts you in the top 0.1% of households, according to an <a href="https://www.ebri.org/" target="_blank" class="icon none">Employee Benefit Research Institute</a> analysis of retirement accounts using the 2019 Survey of Consumer Finances. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="1092" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/d663f044-8f28-4ec7-8377-2302a6c566d6-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> To find out what $5 million buys in retirement, we spoke to retirees around the country with savings in that ballpark.</p><p> Most never expected to be multimillionaires but were diligent about saving from early on in their careers.</p><p> Though they are less concerned about outliving their money than <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/retirement-under-1-million-america-846a6ab6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">many retirees we&#39;ve profiled</a> , they aren&#39;t all living in luxury.有些人已经很多年没有买新衣服了。其他人继续兼职工作。</p><p> They splurge on world travel but, like most older Americans, worry about their health and their families.</p><p> And money alone also doesn&#39;t answer the other question retirees wrestle with: How to find purpose and meaning in this chapter of life? </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/archibald/1JhIu4HsU3kUrK8q6t8nArRD6-qm34M9iySjy14qk7vc-chapter-1.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Paul Shemwell landed in retirement in December after four decades flying commercial planes and jet fighters.</p><p> Though the 65-year-old feels financially secure with about $6.1 million socked away, he hasn&#39;t mapped out a flight plan for what comes next.</p><p> The casual approach is a big change for the former pilot, who honed his strategic thinking skills throughout his 13 years in the Air Force.他的服役经历也教会他仔细权衡自己的选择，这一理念指导着他的退休生活。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/2decacce-5119-4fbc-9b6f-3b2bd857ad6d.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> He stopped flying after 28 years working for <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/LUV" class="">Southwest Airlines</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> but travel remains his passion. He has four trips planned this fall, wanderlust that costs him about $3,000 a month. He spends another roughly $9,000 a month on expenses such as property taxes and home and car insurance.</p><p> His days usually start with a workout or a tennis lesson.作为一名狂热的滑雪爱好者，他已经购买了本赛季的通行证，并计划每年至少进行一次水肺潜水旅行。</p><p> Shemwell turned down several job offers to return to the cockpit, partly because he didn&#39;t need the money.</p><p> He plans to take <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/social-security-payment-increase-cola-2024-retirement-a3fce38e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Social Security</a> upon reaching full retirement age, which will add about $40,000 a year in annual income. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/173863f5-743a-4d58-a219-b57a7e01cbf8.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Life as an empty nester is another big change.他的儿子是大学二年级学生，女儿今年秋天开始上大学。谢姆韦尔已离婚并拥有共同监护权，他表示，他将深入参与孩子的生活作为首要任务。</p><p> His airline schedule gave him the flexibility to attend most of his children&#39;s tennis and football games.现在他们都在上学了，他想去看看他们比赛。</p><p> Shemwell now spends more time with his friends, meeting them for lunch most weekdays.</p><p> He&#39;s not an active trader yet follows the market. His portfolio is <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/it-isnt-just-boomers-lots-of-older-americans-are-stock-obsessed-ca069e1a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">95% stocks</a> , mostly index funds, with a few individual equities such as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="">Apple</a> <span class="company-name-type">.</span> </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832732?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Paul Shemwell has recently taken up tennis again.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Jack Thompson for The Wall Street Journal</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> His father lived into his late 90s so Shemwell is unworried by his heavy stock allocation.</p><p> “My plan is to continue living within or below my means, stay invested and have something to leave to my kids,” he said.</p><p> Shemwell has roughly $300,000 left on the mortgage of his Houston home. He refinanced to a 2.99% interest rate so he is in no rush to pay down the debt.</p><p> He drives a 2016 Infiniti that has about 80,000 miles.这辆车以及他为女儿购买的二手奔驰都是付费的。 He pays his credit-card bill in full each month.</p><p> “I like to keep things simple,” he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/archibald/1JhIu4HsU3kUrK8q6t8nArRD6-qm34M9iySjy14qk7vc-chapter-2.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Jay Myer built up enough savings to retire early from his software-sales career in 2020 after decades of maxing out contributions to his 401(k).</p><p> At 25, Myer read a book by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/vanguards-founder-a-force-of-nature-11547812685?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Vanguard founder John Bogle</a> that espoused low-cost index funds.他也按照著名选股家彼得·林奇的建议购买了个股，“买你所知道的”。 For Myer, now 61, that meant technology stocks and shares in companies he did software deals with, including <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/HD" class="">Home Depot</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> which he purchased decades ago for a split-adjusted $3 a share.</p><p> “I was young to be reading about retirement, but it made a lot of sense to me. If you lower your investment cost, you&#39;ll keep more of the profits,” said Myer, whose retirement account is invested in seven Vanguard index funds.</p><p> He and his wife, Anita, 60, drove used cars and stuck to a budget so Myer could contribute the maximum annual limit to his 401(k) account from age 22 on. Anita worked as a dental hygienist until their second son was born in 2000. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/d872ec8a-8e9f-4719-9763-3d49c3645f1b.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Myer said his decision to retire early was partly inspired by his stepfather, a small-business owner who enjoyed traveling and spending time with grandchildren.</p><p> “He showed me you could let go of the workplace and re-identify yourself,” said Myer.</p><p> Losing a steady paycheck was scary at first. When the market tumbled in 2020, he scrutinized the couple&#39;s every purchase, down to the napkins, but quickly realized that doing so was unnecessary, given their healthy nest egg.</p><p> The couple now has $4.2 million, half in retirement accounts and half in taxable accounts.</p><p> Using the proceeds from the recent sale of their Atlanta home, the couple paid $925,000 for a house in Cary that is 2 miles from their older son&#39;s family, who they see often. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832750?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The Myers love to cook, garden and travel and plan to make improvements to their new home.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Kate Medley for The Wall Street Journal</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> They spend about $130,000 annually, including $5,000 on property taxes.他们每个月在食品上花费约 700 美元，在健康保险上花费 1,000 美元。 (Since they are currently spending from cash reserves, the couple&#39;s taxable income is low enough to qualify them for insurance subsidies.)</p><p> To maximize his monthly benefit, Myer says he&#39;ll wait to take Social Security until age 70.</p><p> The couple considered selling some individual stocks to put more into bonds but were deterred by the capital-gains tax they would owe on their profits. They decided instead to leave their biggest winners to their two sons.</p><p> The Myers, who budget about $20,000 a year for travel, are planning a trip to Spain, where their younger son is living this year.</p><p> Both love to cook and garden. Myer said he is enjoying unstructured time.</p><p> “Now that I have more time, I have learned to embrace boredom and slow down and accept sometimes that reading a book or riding my bike is enough,” he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/archibald/1JhIu4HsU3kUrK8q6t8nArRD6-qm34M9iySjy14qk7vc-chapter-3.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> For Dr. Henry Hwu, work is part of what makes for a satisfying retirement.</p><p> While the Irvine, Calif., surgeon used to put in up to 80 hours a week, he now works part time and around his vacations. “And boy do I like to travel,” Hwu, 72, said.</p><p> An immigrant from Taiwan, Hwu said he and his late wife came to the US in 1979. After studying surgery for five years in Chicago and completing a fellowship in colorectal surgery in Michigan in 1986, Hwu moved to Southern California, where he and his wife raised three children.</p><p> Before reaching his medical practice&#39;s mandatory retirement age of 65, Hwu started reading books (and, he says, Wall Street Journal articles) about retirement. He took up golf and pickleball and bought a guitar, resurrecting a hobby he&#39;d had little time for since medical school.</p><p> But after retiring in 2016, he missed work and began accepting assignments at his former practice.</p><p> Every morning, he asked himself what he would do that day. “我不喜欢那种感觉，”胡说，他的妻子在他退休后不久就去世了。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832859?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Dr. Henry Hwu officially retired in 2016 but continues to work part-time when he&#39;s not traveling.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ryan Young for The Wall Street Journal</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Hwu travels up to three months a year, visiting his 98-year-old mother in Taiwan or exploring Scotland, France, Germany, Japan and Switzerland, where he once bought so much chocolate for friends his suitcase broke.</p><p> Hwu often brings his guitar.最近在伦敦时，他给了一位街头音乐家 20 英镑让他让位，以便他可以演奏 Everly Brothers 的《Let It Be Me》。 “I don&#39;t know how people liked it, but there was an audience standing in front of me,” said Hwu.</p><p> Hwu still enjoys attending medical conferences and reading medical journals.</p><p> At a conference in 2017, he met the only surgeon at a rural hospital in Los Alamos, NM Hwu now travels to Los Alamos to relieve the surgeon for a few days most months. There, he enjoys hiking and seeing his son, an accountant in Albuquerque.</p><p> When home, Hwu takes guitar lessons and often sees his daughter and baby granddaughter. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/f3b9dd2c-d95e-4677-81b1-f14a149509ca.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> His home is worth $1.5 million.他拥有第二套房子，价值 120 万美元，每月租金为 3,500 美元。 He owes about $500,000 on each house but isn&#39;t rushing to pay his mortgages off because the interest rates are below 3%.</p><p> Hwu invests almost all of the more than $1 million in his retirement accounts in equity funds and individual stocks, including Apple, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">Microsoft</a> and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NVDA" class="">Nvidia</a> <span class="company-name-type">.</span></p><p> He gets $2,700 a month in Social Security benefits, which he started taking at 65. He receives about $130,000 a year in pension payments and earned about $300,000 from his per diem work last year.</p><p> Travel is his big splurge, at $100,000 a year. Other expenses come to about $4,000 a month, not counting his mortgage payments.</p><p> He also pays $6,800 annually for a long-term-care insurance policy.</p><p> “With my mom living to 98, there will be a time when I am not able to take care of myself,” he said. “I want to cut down on the burden on my kids.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/archibald/1JhIu4HsU3kUrK8q6t8nArRD6-qm34M9iySjy14qk7vc-chapter-4.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Growing up, Bob Frey never imagined he would retire a multimillionaire.</p><p> After graduating from West Point, he received his master&#39;s degree while on active duty and then his veterinary degree with an Army reserve scholarship and the GI Bill.他担任预备役军官 26 年，60 岁退休。他从 30 多岁开始就用尽了退休计划缴款。</p><p> Times were sometimes tough, like when he borrowed about $150,000 to start a veterinary practice.多年来，他卖掉了三项业务，其中包括两家兽医诊所。 These exits greatly added to his worth, he said.</p><p> These days, Bob, 80, and his wife, Pat Frey, 75, have socked away about $6.1 million, almost half of which is invested in individual retirement accounts.</p><p> Frey gets a $60,000 annual military pension, plus about $14,000 a year in veterans&#39; disability compensation because of hearing loss he developed after serving in Vietnam.这对夫妇从社会保障金中总共领取了约 56,000 美元。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/b82deef5-2fa7-4359-8b0c-802cb8012644.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> “We have more money than we can spend in our lifetimes,” he said.</p><p> The couple, married for more than 30 years, have five adult children between them. 20 世纪 90 年代初，他们搬到了蒙大拿州博兹曼，寻求新的开始并更接近大自然。 Pat continued her nursing career and Bob retrained as a certified financial planner.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> SHARE YOUR THOUGHTS</h4><p> <em>What financial plans are you making for retirement? Tell us about your experience in the form below.</em></p></div></div><p> The Freys, despite their wealth, generally avoid its trappings.鲍勃说他已经大约 20 年没有买过新的运动外套了。 Living in Montana, the couple said they don&#39;t have much use for formal clothes and would rather knock around in jeans and sneakers.帕特经常和朋友一起去大自然散步。</p><p> The Freys expect to spend about $1.5 million to help pay for the education of their nine grandchildren. They also donate roughly $40,000 a year to their favorite charities, including their church. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832798?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Bob Frey goes fly fishing around the world and close to home in the Gallatin River.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Rebecca Stumpf for The Wall Street Journal</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The couple have no debt and don&#39;t tinker much with their investments, of which about 70% is invested in stock funds. They may leave about $1 million to charity upon their deaths, Bob said.</p><p> The Freys, too, value travel and allocate about $35,000 a year to seeing the world.他们曾五次访问新西兰，鲍勃经常将他对飞钓的热爱与阿拉斯加、墨西哥和南美洲的旅行结合起来。</p><p> They also enjoy separate trips with their friends.帕特经常与朋友一起前往欧洲和加拉帕戈斯群岛。 She skips Bob&#39;s hunting trips.</p><p> “I have no desire to sleep in a tent and carry an elk out of the woods,” she said.</p><p> Write to Veronica Dagher at <a href="mailto:Veronica.Dagher@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Veronica.Dagher@wsj.com</a> and Anne Tergesen at <a href="mailto:anne.tergesen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">anne.tergesen@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
